summary:
And here are the Minior Shell photos!

Info recap: in and out of his shell, Minior is 16in from tip to tip, making him lifesize...
caption:
And here are the Minior Shell photos!

Info recap: in and out of his shell, Minior is 16in from tip to tip, making him lifesize according to the Pokedex! His shell is completely removable from his core and features all of the details you see in the game/anime from his markings, cracked detailing and more!

Minior is so amazingly cuddly and plush whether in or out of his shell, and I’m still so over the moon proud of this project~ while there is a 99% chance I’ll never again make a Minior like this where the shell is removable, I am open to the idea of making Minior Cores in the future, or even just his shell form!

My amigurumi orders are currently closed, but should reopen in 4-5 weeks at TheTallGrass.etsy.com!

Reviewing my personal opinion on every single Pokemon! Yes, all 809 of them!
(Mostly) Daily Uploads, 3 PM EST.

summary: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Mienfoo and Mienshao
title: Let’s Talk About Pokemon - Mienfoo and Mienshao
body:
619: Mienfoo

Mienfoo’s always been a Pokemon I’ve flopped back and forth on. I remember not being super impressed when I first saw the thing before growing to like it. Only to forget it existed for a while, then liking it again when I remembered it existed. Which is perhaps strange, considering the Fighting type has struggled to get a hit off with me just because the general Fighting aesthetic is far from my own. So here we finally have some cutesy weasel thing that knows kung fu. And I kinda gloss over it for the most part, apart from when I remember it. Heh.

There’s no denying it’s a cute little thing though. Not the most creative critter out there but, like I said, when the Fighting type’s been wrestling to get me to like anything out of them, I guess the next best thing is to pander to my liking of cute little weasels. Mienfoo’s got plenty of its own merits though! The face is adorable, and I do like how the fur kind of looks like it’s wearing robes without it looking uncomfortably uncanny.

Personal Score: 8/10

Sure, let’s go with 8.

620: Mienshao

And perhaps part of why Mienfoo gets overlooked by me is how much Mienshao takes the cake. Honestly, at least to me, Mienshao here is everything Lucario wishes it was. Lucario had a pitiable attempt at being an elegant anthropomorphic Fighting type while falling flat on its face cause it’s also trying to be a tough macho thing. But Mienshao looks both more elegant and more animal-like to pull off the look for more, well, elegantly. It has nice flowing shapes, and they about picked the best animal for the thing they were going for. Being a long-bodied mustelid like a stoat or weasel. Combining that with kung-fu moves turned out to work far more than you’d think. It’s a master of long features which sells the look all the better.

One of Mienshao’s more interesting aspects is its long “sleeves”, basically having an extra extension of skin and/or fur hanging off their wrists, which it also uses to fight with. That’s pretty dang cool! While it’s strange to think about it too hard, in the same way it’s weird to think Sylveon has fleshy ribbon appendages, I think that not only gives it just the right touch of fanatical so that this thing isn’t literally just a kung-fu fighting stoat, but a little bit more. But it also pulls off the look without looking too bizarre and out of place. These natural robe sleeves are a true extension of itself, and they work really well to give it a better look overall.

Personal Score: 9/10

Clearly the coolest Fighting Type.

Overall:

Not too shabby a pair! Mienfoo could have a little more going for it, but it’s nice when a fully evolved form is considerably well-built off of the first form.
